\label{coronontor}
For any arithmetic-type sequence $(e_n)$, the followings are equivalent:
\begin{itemize}
\item[$(i)$] $t_{(e_n)}(\T)\not= t_{(d_n)}(\T)$.
\item[$(ii)$] $t_{(e_n)}(\T)$ contains non-torsion elements.
\item[$(iii)$] $t_{(e_n)}(\T)$ is uncountable.
\item[$(iv)$] $|t_{(e_n)}(\T)|=\mathfrak{c}$
\item[$(v)$] $|t_{(e_n)}(\T)\setminus t_{(d_n)}(\T)|=\mathfrak{c}$.
\end{itemize}

